Hey @Anish,
feedbacks, need to be addresses, so you can close pr fix and again do the pr
What is better now:
singleton/global cached logger is gone; latest utility creates fresh instances with create_status_logger() / create_metric_logger()

context is more generic now; utility takes a context dict instead of forcing fixed fields everywhere
with_context() now gives a new scoped logger, which is much cleaner than mutating shared state

status normalization is cleaner now; hardcoded "no file" from old version is no longer the utility default, and pipeline can pass its own allowed statuses like no_file
On log bucketing, not bad

log_debug() → level DEBUG
log_running(), log_success(), log_info() → INFO
log_warning() → WARNING
log_error(), log_failed(), log_exception() → ERROR behavior, though status is still emitted as failed not error
What is still not ideal:
regular logger is still alive in real path, not just local debug/fallback
import-time warnings/errors still go through regular logger
helper fallbacks still do logger.info/warning/error when status_logger is missing

so it is not fully “Aura for everything” yet, it is still mixed
Summary:

utility file: good improvement, much closer to what you asked
data transfer lambda: better, but still partially mixed with regular logger
level mapping: yes, mostly correctly bucketed
main remaining issue: make MikAura the main path for all runtime pipeline logs, and keep stdlib logger only for very early import/init or true local fallback
